{"id": 1657, "title": "Ticket #1657: Update condor's installer to use WiX", "description": "<blockquote>\nTicket to track work/progress on WiX port of installer.\n\n<p>modifications will be made on: V7_5-cmake-stage-publicbranch</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2010-Sep-22 10:06:57 by tstclair:</em> <br/>\n\nPATCH to ...Modules\\CPackWiX.cmake\n\n<p>I will update all files referenced in wiki.\n\n</p><p></p><div class=\"code\">\n<pre class=\"code\">IF ( CPACK_WIX_WXS_FILES )\n\n        foreach ( _ITEM ${CPACK_WIX_WXS_FILES} )\n\t\t#get just the file name which will be used for compiled .wxs objects\n\t\tstring(REGEX MATCH \"[^/]*$\" _wxs_file \"${_ITEM}\")\n\t\tif (NOT CPACK_WIX_OBJS)\n\t\t\tset (CPACK_WIX_OBJS ${_wxs_file})\n\t\telse ()\n\t\t\tset (CPACK_WIX_OBJS \"${CPACK_WIX_OBJS} ${_wxs_file}\")\n\t\tendif()\n\tendforeach(_ITEM)\n\n        # transform to compatible input to command line utils\n\tstring(REPLACE \".wxs\" \".wixobj\" CPACK_WIX_OBJS \"${CPACK_WIX_OBJS}\" )\n\tstring(REPLACE \";\" \" \" CPACK_WIX_OBJS \"${CPACK_WIX_OBJS}\" )\n\t# cmake list -&gt; \" \" for command line input\n\tstring(REPLACE \";\" \" \" CPACK_WIX_WXS_FILES \"${CPACK_WIX_WXS_FILES}\" )\n\nENDIF( CPACK_WIX_WXS_FILES )\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p></p><hr/>\n<em>2010-Nov-21 21:34:40 by tstclair:</em> <br/>\n\nI'm going to be reviewing all the recent mods.\n\n<p></p><hr/>\n<em>2010-Nov-23 09:51:02 by tstclair:</em> <br/>\n\nThere appears to be a config issue.  If it's possible to make ifThenElse blocks in the generic config that would solve this problem.  Otherwise we will need to provide a generic windows config.\n\n<p></p><hr/>\n<em>2011-Jan-25 14:42:18 by ziliang:</em> <br/>\n\nTODO:\n* Investigate why the estimated disk space usage is so inflated.\n* Create a separate dialog chain for upgrades.\n* Persist installation answers for future usage for upgrade purposes.\n* Stuff registry for kbdd startup.  Currently kbdd itself acts as a failsafe and will do the registry stuffing itself if need be.\n* Punch hole for condor_hdfs in installer.  Doesn't matter for 7.5.5 since condor_hdfs doesn't work anyway on Windows in that version.\n<hr/>\n<em>2011-Jan-27 14:50:47 by danb:</em> <br/>\n\nBulk change of target version from v070505 to v070506 using ./ticket-target-mover.\n<hr/>\n<em>2011-Feb-01 16:19:13 by tannenba:</em> <br/>\n\nBulk change of target version from v070506 to NULL using ./ticket-target-mover.\n\n<p></p><hr/>\n<em>2011-Mar-30 15:12:30 by tstclair:</em> <br/>\n\nI think you can close this one out now.</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">\n<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=1979\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('1979'); return false;\" title=\"Installer throws a warning if the firewall service is deactivated.\">#1979</a></span></td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"center\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon ptr1\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\">\nInstaller throws a warning if the firewall service is deactivated.</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2011-Feb-24 14:11</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/284edf288a7545602e601855cdf6e841e660910f\">[20742]</a></span>: Fix HDFS directory paths in installer. Ticket <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=1657\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('1657'); return false;\" title=\"Update condor's installer to use WiX\">#1657</a></span>.  (By Ziliang Guo )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\